verbose_text: The excessive inflammatory response of the immature intestine is in part due to a developmental under-expression of IkB XREF_BIBR as well as overexpression of the NFkB / MyD88 innate inflammatory genes (TLR2, TLR4, MyD88, TRAF-6, NFkB1 and IL-8) and under-expression of negative regulator genes (SIGIRR, IRAK-M, A-20 and TOLLIP) in fetal intestine relative to older children XREF_BIBR.
